"'''Murder in Slushtime'''" is a short story written by [[Barbara Hambly]] (with illustrations by [[Doug Shuler]]), originally published in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 14|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 14]] by [[West End Games]] in [[August]] [[1997]], and since released online at [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]]. It takes place in [[13 ABY/Legends|13 ABY]].

==Plot summary==
Stranded on [[Gamorr/Legends|Gamorr]] during slushtime, [[Callista Ming]] is part of the crew of the ''[[Zicreex]]''. One of the other [[Gamorrean/Legends|Gamorrean]] crew, [[Guth]], is accused of [[Death/Legends|murder]], and the rest of them are guilty by association and taken [[Prisoner/Legends|prisoner]] by a hostile [[Warlord/Legends|warlord]]. Callista manages to convince the [[Kufbrug|wife]] of the slain [[Vrokk]] to let her investigate the murder. Callista learns that Guth, a boar, would not likely have [[Poison/Legends|poisoned]] Vrokk as boars are not known for their brilliance. Visiting a local [[Poet/Legends|poet]], [[Sebastin Onyx]], Callista picks up information on the motive and method of the [[Assassin/Legends|killer]]. She and Kufbrug hold a vigil over the room where Vrokk was slain and a [[kheilwar]] appears, a nocturnal [[Hunting/Legends|hunting]] creature. Callista and Kufbrug fight and corner the kheilwar until it [[Changeling/Legends|shape-shifts]] into the others it has seen, which reveals the murderers to be [[Rog]], Vrokk's brother, and [[Gundruk]], Kufbrug's daughter, who had planned on also killing Kufbrug to take over her holdings.

